== Births == * {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1507]] {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōuchi Yoshitaka|ja|大内義隆|12=draft|12=draft}}, a daimyō (died [[1551]]). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|寛政|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1798]] {{ill|January 1|ja|1月1日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Utagawa Kuniyoshi|ja|歌川国芳|12=draft|12=draft}}, an ukiyo-e artist (died [[1861]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1819]] {{ill|December 31|ja|12月31日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Miyaji Tsunetoki|ja|宮地常磐|12=draft|12=draft}}, head of the Chōkō-tenma Shrine (died [[1890]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1836]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Sakamoto Ryōma|ja|坂本龍馬|12=draft|12=draft}}, a statesman of the Bakumatsu period (died [[1867]]). * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1847]] {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōtsuki Fumihiko|ja|大槻文彦|12=draft|12=draft}}, a linguist and author of "Gengai" (died [[1928]]). * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1861]] {{ill|December 16|ja|12月16日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ochiai Naofumi|ja|落合直文|12=draft|12=draft}}, a waka poet (died [[1903]]). * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1863]] {{ill|December 25|ja|12月25日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shiga Jūkō|ja|志賀重昂|12=draft|12=draft}}, a geographer and politician (died [[1927]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1586]] {{ill|December 25|ja|12月25日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Yoshikawa Motoharu|ja|吉川元春|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Sengoku-period warrior and the second son of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|毛利元就|12=draft|12=draft}} (born [[1530]]). * {{ill|Jōō|ja|承応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1654]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsunaga Sadatoku|ja|松永貞徳|12=draft|12=draft}}, a haiku poet and classicist (born [[1571]]). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 10|ja|12月10日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Sakamoto Ryōma|ja|坂本龍馬|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Bakumatsu statesman (born [[1836]]).
