{{Lunisolar November}} '''November 15''' is the 15th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=draft}} the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft}} 19th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1614]] {{ill|December 15|ja|12月15日|12=draft}}) – During the {{ill|Osaka Winter Campaign|ja|大坂冬の陣|12=draft}}, the army of {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|12=draft}} set out to attack {{ill|Osaka Castle|ja|大坂城|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 10|ja|12月10日|12=draft}}) – In the [[Ōmiya Incident]], both {{ill|Sakamoto Ryōma|ja|坂本龍馬|12=draft}} and {{ill|Nakaoka Shintarō|ja|中岡慎太郎|12=draft}} were attacked; Ryōma died on that day, and Shintarō died three days later. * {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|December 15|ja|12月15日|12=draft}}) – The {{ill|National Bank Ordinance|ja|国立銀行条例|12=draft}} was enacted. * In Meiji 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} 1872, 12月15日) – The year of the accession of {{ill|Emperor Jimmu|ja|神武天皇|12=draft}} was established as the Japanese era of [[Kigen]] ({{ill|Jimmu Tennō Sokui Kigen|ja|神武天皇即位紀元|1=Japanese imperial year|12=draft}}).
