== Births == * {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1507]] {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Ōuchi Yoshitaka|ja|大内義隆|qq=}}, a daimyō (died [[1551]]). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|寛政|qq=}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1798]] {{ill|January 1|ja|1月1日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Utagawa Kuniyoshi|ja|歌川国芳|qq=}}, an ukiyo-e artist (died [[1861]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1819]] {{ill|December 31|ja|12月31日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Miyaji Tsunetoki|ja|宮地常磐|qq=}}, head of the Chōkō-tenma Shrine (died [[1890]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1836]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Sakamoto Ryōma|ja|坂本龍馬|qq=}}, a statesman of the Bakumatsu period (died [[1867]]). * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|qq=}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1847]] {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Ōtsuki Fumihiko|ja|大槻文彦|qq=}}, a linguist and author of "Gengai" (died [[1928]]). * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1861]] {{ill|December 16|ja|12月16日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Ochiai Naofumi|ja|落合直文|qq=}}, a waka poet (died [[1903]]). * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1863]] {{ill|December 25|ja|12月25日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Shiga Jūkō|ja|志賀重昂|qq=}}, a geographer and politician (died [[1927]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1586]] {{ill|December 25|ja|12月25日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Yoshikawa Motoharu|ja|吉川元春|qq=}}, a Sengoku-period warrior and the second son of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|毛利元就|qq=}} (born [[1530]]). * {{ill|Jōō|ja|承応|qq=}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1654]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Matsunaga Sadatoku|ja|松永貞徳|qq=}}, a haiku poet and classicist (born [[1571]]). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|qq=}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 10|ja|12月10日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Sakamoto Ryōma|ja|坂本龍馬|qq=}}, a Bakumatsu statesman (born [[1836]]).
