== Births == * [[:en:Eishō (Muromachi period)|Eishō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1507|1507]] [[:en:December 18|December 18]]) – [[:en:Ōuchi Yoshitaka|Ōuchi Yoshitaka]], a daimyō (died [[:en:1551|1551]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1798|1798]] [[:en:January 1|January 1]]) – [[:en:Utagawa Kuniyoshi|Utagawa Kuniyoshi]], an ukiyo-e artist (died [[:en:1861|1861]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1819|1819]] [[:en:December 31|December 31]]) – {{ill|Miyaji Tsunetoki|ja|宮地常磐|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyaji Tsunetoki|qq=}}, head of the Chōkō-tenma Shrine (died [[1890]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1836|1836]] [[:en:January 3|January 3]]) – [[:en:Sakamoto Ryōma|Sakamoto Ryōma]], a statesman of the Bakumatsu period (died [[1867]]). * [[:en:Kōka|Kōka]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1847|1847]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]]) – [[:en:Ōtsuki Fumihiko|Ōtsuki Fumihiko]], a linguist and author of "Gengai" (died [[1928]]). * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1861|1861]] [[:en:December 16|December 16]]) – [[:en:Ochiai Naobumi|Ochiai Naofumi]], a waka poet (died [[1903]]). * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[:en:December 25|December 25]]) – [[:en:Shiga Shigetaka|Shiga Jūkō]], a geographer and politician (died [[1927]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 14th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1586|1586]] [[:en:December 25|December 25]]) – [[:en:Kikkawa Motoharu|Yoshikawa Motoharu]], a Sengoku-period warrior and the second son of [[:en:Mōri Motonari|Mōri Motonari]] (born [[:en:1530|1530]]). * [[:en:Jōō (Edo period)|Jōō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1654|1654]] [[:en:January 3|January 3]]) – [[:en:Matsunaga Teitoku|Matsunaga Sadatoku]], a haiku poet and classicist (born [[:en:1571|1571]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1867]] [[:en:December 10|December 10]]) – [[:en:Sakamoto Ryōma|Sakamoto Ryōma]], a Bakumatsu statesman (born [[:en:1836|1836]]).
== Commemorations == ⒈ 七五三
